context: <user> I will be in Cambridge and am looking for some places to go in the centre while I visit. <system> I'd be happy to help you pick one! There are over 40 attractions in city centre; what type of activity are you interested in? <user> I don't really care. Can you suggest something? <system> How about a museum? Or we have some terrific colleges you could visit. There's always the theatre as well. <user> How about a theatre? Can you give me the post code and phone number for one, please? <system> The Cambridge Arts Theatre is located at 6 saint edward's passage in postcode cb23pj. Their phone number is 01223503333. <user> Thank you! Can you help me find a hotel to stay in? I need it to have free wifi. <system> Just about every lodging in town has internet (it's 2017, after all!). Do you have a certain area or price range in mind?<user> It needs to be in the same area as theatre and have free parking. I dont care about the price. <system> Okay its address is located at 6 saint edward's passage and its postal code is cb23pj.<user> Can you book it for me? Just for one person starting on Wednesday for 5 nights. <system> I'm sorry, none of the hotels in the centre are free on those dates. Would you like to try a different number of days?<user> Can you try for just 2 nights then? <system> Your booking at the Alexander bed and breakfast was successful, the reference number is L60GOSEU .<user> Can I please book a taxi to get to the hotel? <system> Sure. What time would you like to be picked up from Cambridge Arts Theatre?<user> I'd actually like to be picked up from Alexander bed and breakfast by 15:30. <system> I have booked a black BMW to pick you up. The contact number is 07334398349.<user> That's all for today. Thanks for your help! <system>
